In fact, it turns out the Pusher protocol is all JSON, so you can autogenerate the code.<p>Here&#x27;s a Pusher message.<p><pre><code>  {
    &quot;event&quot;: &quot;pusher:error&quot;,
    &quot;data&quot;: {
      &quot;message&quot;: String,
      &quot;code&quot;: Integer
    }
  }
</code></pre>
Here&#x27;s the corresponding Haskell.<p><pre><code>  {-# LANGUAGE DeriveGeneric #-}

  import GHC.Generics

  -- a generic wrapper type for all Pusher events
  data Event a = Event {
      eventType :: Text,
      eventData :: a
    } deriving (Generic)

  instance ToJSON a   => ToJSON (Event a)
  instance FromJSON a => FromJSON (Event a)


  data Error = Error {
      message :: Text,
      code :: Integer
    } deriving (Generic)

  instance ToJSON   Error
  instance FromJSON Error</code></pre>
